  "mixStrategy": "THREE-TRACK BLUES RELAXATION MIX STRATEGY:\n\nFREQUENCY SEPARATION:\n- Electric Bass (100-300Hz): Provides the warm, deep foundation with a relaxed walking bass feel. Stays in MIDI 33-48 range (A1-C3). Root motion anchors each chord change, with chromatic approach tones and 5ths as passing tones. Slow, deliberate quarter-note walking with occasional half-notes for breathing space.\n- Piano Comping (300Hz-2kHz): Fills the harmonic mid-range with dominant 7th voicings in MIDI 48-67 range (C3-G4). Comps on beats 2 and 4 in shuffle style, leaving space for melody. Voiced with 3rds and 7ths prominent for that blues color. Gentle velocity (40-60) for relaxation warmth.\n- Steel Guitar Melody (1kHz-8kHz): Floats above in MIDI 60-79 range (C4-G5). Plays lyrical blues licks with long sustains (2-6s), grace-note bends (chromatic approach from below), and call-and-response phrasing. Velocity 45-65 for gentle expressiveness.\n\nRHYTHMIC INTERLOCK:\n- Bass walks steady quarter/half notes, providing the pulse\n- Piano comps on beats 2&4, locking with bass on chord changes\n- Melody plays between piano hits, breathing in the spaces, with long sustained blue notes\n\nHARMONIC UNITY (12-bar blues in A at 61 BPM, ~0.984s per beat, ~3.93s per bar):\n- Bars 1-4 (0.0-15.7s): A7 \u2014 Energy 0.3\u21920.5, gentle opening\n- Bars 5-6 (15.7-23.6s): D7 \u2014 Energy 0.5\u21920.6, warming up\n- Bars 7-8 (23.6-31.5s): A7 \u2014 Energy 0.7, emotional peak\n- Bar 9 (31.5-35.4s): E7 \u2014 Energy 0.7\u21920.6, turnaround begins\n- Bar 10 (35.4-39.3s): D7 \u2014 Energy 0.6\u21920.4, winding down\n- Bars 11-12 (39.3-45.0s): A7 \u2014 Energy 0.4, gentle resolution\n\nENERGY ARC: All three tracks follow the same arc \u2014 sparse/quiet at start, building together to bar 7-9 peak, then gently fading. Bass gets slightly more active, piano voicings get fuller, melody gets more expressive at the peak, then all relax together.",
